   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE INTRINSIC BUILDING UP OF THE CHURCH</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR ITS ORGANIC FUNCTION Scripture Reading: Eph 4:8-16; 1 Cor 12:28; Acts 13:1; Rom 12:4-8; 1 Cor 12:4-11; 14:4b, 12; Eph 1:23b OUTLINE The intrinsic building up of the church: By the ascended Head giving the gifts Eph 4:8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>By the Head-given gifts the apostles, prophets, evangelists, and shepherds and teachers perfecting the saints Eph 4:11-12: In the local churches 1 Cor 12:28; Acts 13:1.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Unto the work of the ministry the building up of the organic Body of Christ Eph 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Until all the members of Christ arrive at: The oneness of the faith and of the full knowledge of the Son of God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>A full-grown man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ the church as the organic Body of Christ Eph 4:13.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Through all the perfected members of the Body of Christ Eph 4:14-16: Being no longer babes tossed by waves and carried about by every wind of teaching in the sleight of men, in craftiness with a view to a system of error v. 14.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>But holding to truth in love to grow up into the Head, Christ, in all things v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Out from the Head v. 16a.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>All the Body, joined closely together through every joint of the rich supply, and knit together through the operation in measure of each part, causing the growth of the Body unto the building up of itself in love v. 16b.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The organic function of the church: In the organic Body of Christ Rom 12:4-8.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In the local expressions of the organic Body of Christ 1 Cor 12:28.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>By the move of the Triune God: In the operations of God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Through the ministries of the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>With the gifts of the Spirit in His manifestations to the members of the organic Body of Christ 1 Cor 12:4-11.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>For the building up of the church as the organic Body of Christ, the fullness of the One who fills all in all 1 Cor 14:4b, 12; Eph 1:23b.</S>
   </TEXT>
